    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="725"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                    <dateline rend="right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Your 49, August 3, 1 p. m. All I can say at present is that American
                    Government is preparing a note to the British Government in regard to
                    maintenance of trade with neutral countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
